    "text": "Hot take that I'm not sure that I completely believe: **when writing software tests, only write tests for your actual API**.\r\n\r\nGood:\r\n\r\n```javascript\r\nconst api = require('../src');\r\n\r\nassert(api.randomInteger(0, 100), 42);\r\n````\r\n\r\nBad:\r\n\r\n```javascript\r\nconst range = require('../src/lib/range/')\r\n\r\nassert(range.createRange(0, 100)[0], 0);\r\nassert(range.createRange(0, 100).length, 100);\r\nassert(range.createRange(0, 100)[100], 99);\r\n```\r\n\r\nIf your `createRange()` function is so complicated that it needs its own specific tests, maybe it should be its own module with its own API.\r\n\r\n#software #tdd",
